<br>
Any given camp usually has a mob or two up - otherwise it's not a good camp (lack of pulls).<br>
<br>
In the case of swarm kiting, the bard is continuously killing for extended periods of time. Usually by the time the bard is finished, the mobs he/she killed initially have respawned and are ready to be kited. Which means that although a group may happen to move in on a kited area and see some mobs up, it doesn't mean they aren't being kited.<br>
<br>
Think of an AE camp. To make the AE's efficient, a lot of mobs have to be pulled at once. Even if the different mobs have staggered respawn times, the group has to wait till all of them are back up. That doesn't mean a group can just move in and kill one of the quicker respawns just because 'they aren't being killed in that particular wave'. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barrandaam>BarrandAam</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mywhimsy.com/boards/dv/BarrEpic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I do not do combines for <BR> free so stop asking me or<BR> i slam this goldenrod <BR> where the sun dont shine</span><br>  Posts: 796<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/5/03 4:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1599.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~spellbinders/_uimages/BarJae.gif width=100 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Of course, were he really doing this, he would have run back to collect the mobs as they respawned. Amazingly, he wasnt even in the zone for a chunk of that time. <p><div align=center> I am<a target=“new” href = 
