<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Face it, you've got a bard with a faggot name to begin with who can't pull while running in circles (which is something I can't figure out, if you can park your swarm by making a pet, what prevents you from charming near your pull site  )<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I addressed this. If you pull while your charming, your pet will be left behind. A given pet only lasts about 12 to 18 seconds. That means you won't be given accurate hp updates for when to break charm, and, when charm breaks (either because you broke it by pure blind luck, or they killed it) those mobs will likely be in the water somewhere you can't see, on the way toward where you're trying to pull.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>who can't kite his pulls in the vicinity of his camp so he goes where you can't even see his little circlejerk in action<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well that's again not supported by the facts. To quote, yet again, an earlier passage, this one Liberachi's:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Well, anyway, I see this group (all from the same guild) come up and make camp in the middle of my pull through area.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If he can see them, they most certainly must have seen him.<br>
<br>
Although this is out of order, the first part of your statement makes a false implication; that his lack of skill determines his inability to kite in that camp.<br>
<br>
The geography of that area forbids it. Charm can't land when the mobs are in the water, and in order to swarm kite, you have to go in circles large enough such that they don't hit you. That specific locale has the above-water terrain shaped like an isthmus - making it impossible to have the mobs completely out of the water at all times.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>, who finds time to bitch and whine even though he can't type while doing the aforementioned circlejerk<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My suspicion is that he completely stopped gaining exp from the swarm kite just so he could chat in /ooc. If you want the reasoning as to why the fact that he can do that still doesn't justify his lack of communication earlier, see my above posts, or read the quoted selection:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also, consider the precedent it sets. Bard swarm kiting is dangerous *when* you add having to type. Consider if a bard would have to &quot;call&quot; that spot every time a group moves in. Now consider what happens if, in a busy zone like PoD apparently is (on your server), a new group moves in every 20 or so minutes. That means, every 20 minutes a bard has to completely stop any and all exp gain to 'discuss' with a group the fact that (a) he's camped there, and (b) has a right to camp it, and also subject themselves to a great degree of danger.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and who resorts to training when he doesn't get his way and mommy can't help him out. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again I quote from above:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yes. But the method by which he trained them is what differentiates him from any random form of retribution. He trains them by doing that which he had been doing for hours, namely pulling a swarm to kill it.<br>
<br>
To make this simpler: Had he pulled a swarm for purely kiting purposes, without the intent to kill the group, the result would have been identical. The group would have died. What this reveals is that the group and he were in direct competition over a camp he had a rightful claim to. Not just that he trained them, he trained them because they relied on the following:<br>
<br>
If he tries to KS them, as a way to take back the camp, he'll fail miserably.<br>
<br>
If he tries to petition, the GM's will enforce a rotation, which ultimately will benefit them more than he.<br>
<br>
They tried to force his hand, so he played the cards he was dealt. They continued pulling to a location he had a legitimate claim to, and he continued his method of killing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Where in this entire thread, or in the thread on your little bard site, should I see indicators that this yeast infection should get any sympathy, mercy, or reasonable expectation of ever getting guilded? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't care what he gets, or doesn't get. That is completely irrelevant at this stage.<br>
<br>
In fact, I would say he shouldn't get either sympathy or mercy. All he needed, he has - reasonable justification.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>? Go ahead and play &quot;pick your quotes&quot;, it doesn't alter the fact that I see two faggot bards, one who's a PoMS and should be added to the list, and one that should be banned for not playing here anyways. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Your decision to ignore reality and persist in a delusion reveals something in you, if you aren't too afraid to look. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dieldekoenig>Diel DeKoenig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>(e) Drano makes good koolaid </span><br>  Posts: 420<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/6/03 11:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1599.topic&index=88>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bards from other servers make God cry</span><hr size=1> You are a fucking shitstain idiot.<br>
